The paper discusses mobile-edge computing (MEC) systems, which involve the integration of mobile devices and cloud computing. This topic is closely related to several sub-categories in computer science, including networked systems (cs.NI), distributed computing (cs.DC), control systems (cs.SY), information theory (cs.IT), and architecture (cs.AR). Given the focus on networked systems and distributed computing, cs.NI and cs.DC are the most likely sub-categories. However, the paper also discusses optimization and control algorithms, which suggests that cs.SY and cs.IT are also relevant. Finally, the paper touches on hardware and system design, which aligns with cs.AR.
